headline: What Analysts Think Is Changing The Story For Full House Resorts (FLL)
summary: Why Full House Resorts' Price Target Story Just Got More Nuanced Analysts have kept Full House Resorts' fair value intact at US$3.75 per share, but they have made subtle tweaks to the model behind it, including a slightly lower discount rate and steady revenue growth assumptions. These refinements suggest that while the core valuation view is unchanged, the risk and reward balance is now seen as more neutral. This aligns with the shift to a Hold stance and a US$3 price target that already...
